              <span id="hs_cos_wrapper_post_body" class="hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text" style="" data-hs-cos-general-type="meta_field" data-hs-cos-type="rich_text"><p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png" alt="The best charts for colorblind viewers - discover the right color palette for your data visualization" width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-colorblind-viewers-featured-image-1200x628.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>How do we see the world in colors? It all starts with the light. The light can come from the Sun, fire or a lamp sending waves of different lengths. The surfaces around us have different capacities for absorbing wavelengths, so some of the waves are absorbed, while others are reflected. The ones that are reflected can be perceived by our eyes. These waves go through the cornea and pupil and hit the retina. The retina consists of cones and rods. Cones are the ones that are responsible for color perception. The combination of waves that hit the cones form in our brain the perception of color.<img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png" alt="The three types of cones responsible for color perception." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-cones-and-colors.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<!--more-->
<p style="font-size: 14px; text-align: center;"><span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #666666;"><em>There are three types of cones: T</em></span><span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #666666;"><em>he first type is sensitive to long wavelengths (starting from red, peaking at yellow, and declining at green). The second type is sensitive to middle wavelengths (starting at orange, peaking at green, and declining at blue). The third type is sensitive to short wavelengths (starting at green and peaking at blue).</em></span></p>
<p style="font-size: 14px; text-align: center;">&nbsp;</p>
<div data-hs-responsive-table="true" style="overflow-x: auto; max-width: 100%; width: 100%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
