<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="what-colors-can-they-see" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;">What colors can color blind people see?</h2>
<p>Actually, it depends on what type of cones don't work. There are three common types: protanopia (red-blind), deuteranopia (green-blind), and tritanopia (blue-blind). There can also be an intermediate state, color weakness - when the colors can be distinguished but some of the hue details are lost. There’s also a very rare state when all the cones are not working and the person is completely color blind – it’s called complete achromatopsia. In the next picture, the simulation of what colors can color blind people see is presented.</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png" alt="Colorblindness depends on what type of cones don't work. The three common types are protanopia, deuteranopia, and trianopia" width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>There are around 300 million people in the world who are colorblind. About 8% of men and 0.5% of women are colorblind, so making your chart color blind safe is a reasonable thing to do.</p>
<div class="hs-embed-wrapper" data-service="insights.datylon" data-script-embed="true" data-responsive="true" style="position: relative; overflow: hidden; width: 100%; height: auto; padding: 0px; max-width: 720px; min-width: 256px; display: block; margin: auto; max-height: 421px;"><div class="hs-embed-content-wrapper"><article data-datylon="a97dd4c1-6672-44d8-bae1-4592ed326553"><img src="https://insights.datylon.com/datystore/api/v1/publications/uuFFku0yZVOpfdTBZnJE2A/template" alt="There are around 300 million people in the world who are color blind. About 8% of men and 0.5% of women are color blind."><a href="https://insights.datylon.com/stories/uuFFku0yZVOpfdTBZnJE2A">Color blind stats</a></article><script src="https://insights.datylon.com/assets/embed.js" async></script></div></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="color-blind-palette" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h2 style="text-align: justify; font-size: 30px;">Color blind palette</h2>
<p style="text-align: justify;">The picture below shows that for all of the types of color blindness there is a pair of colors that can be distinguished – red and blue – these are color blind safe colors. As for the green, it is the number one among the colors to avoid for the color blind. Most of the issues for colorblind people come from the prevalence of red-and-green combinations as a pair of opposites in design. The first rule of making a palette for colorblind – avoid combining red and green. So if you’re aiming to create a color blind-friendly palette try to use only two basic hues: blue and red (orange and yellow will also fit). The other colors should be made out of these two hues. All the variations can be made by using different saturation or lightness of the basic color. Based on these rules we’ve created a color blind palette and checked it for three color blindness types.&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png" alt="For all of the types of color blindness, there is a pair of colors that can be distinguished – red and blue – these are color blind safe colors." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-color-blindness-palette.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>As you can see the palette worked for all types of color blindness, but you should always be aware that the variation of color-blind colors can vary significantly from person to person, so it’s always important to double-check. If you have a friend who is colorblind – ask for feedback. Alternatively, you can look up a colorblind community online and reach out to them. Don’t forget about people with complete color blindness and remember that 100% best colors for colorblind are black and white. So if your visualization works in greyscale you should be safe. Another advantage of using black and white data visualization is that they’re print-ready. But remember, if the palette is grayscale one should use other tools to distinguish chart elements. <br><br>There are a few tools that can help you to check your visuals. For this article, a <a href="https://www.color-blindness.com/2016/10/27/new-release-of-color-blindness-simulator/">color-blind simulator</a> was used from the Colorblindor website. There’s also a helpful internal tool in Adobe Illustrator. You can access it under <strong>View &gt; Proof Setup &gt; Color-Blindness - Protanopia-type or Deuteranopia-type.</strong><strong><span style="background-color: #d9ead3;"><br></span></strong></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: normal;"><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png" alt="Helpful internal tool in Adobe Illustrator that can help you to check if your visuals are color blind friendly." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-Illutstrator-tools.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></span></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;">&nbsp;</h2>
<a id="how-to-make-them-color-blind-friendly" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;">How to make charts color blind friendly?</h2>
<p><strong>Use shapes and icons</strong> as an addition or alternative to color-coding. In case one needs to use colors that are not perceptible by colorblind users, a chart can be saved by using icons as an addition to color, duplicating its informational function.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png" alt="Make your charts color blind friendly: use shapes and icons as an addition or alternative to color-coding." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-use-icons.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Typically, it’s better to <strong>use direct labels</strong> instead of a legend – it saves the time and attention of a reader. Another advantage of direct labels is its ability to fix the usage of palettes that are not color blind friendly.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png" alt="Make your charts color blind friendly: use direct labels instead of a legend." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-direct-labels.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>For line charts and their variations, <strong>dashed lines</strong> and <strong>lines with various stroke thicknesses</strong> can be a very helpful alternative to coloring.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png" alt="Make your charts color blind friendly: dashed lines and lines with various stroke thicknesses are a very helpful alternative to coloring for line charts." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dashed-line.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>Adding strokes around chart elements</strong> might also help to distinguish one element from the other if the color might look the same for color-blind users.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png" alt="Make your charts color blind friendly: add strokes around chart elements to distinguish one element from the other." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-separate-elements.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>If the usage of color is inevitable try to <strong>use a single hue</strong> <strong>palette. </strong>It will make the chart readable for all kinds of color blindness including monochromacy (when no color can be recognized). The second option is to <strong>use a red-yellow-blue palette</strong>. It will work for all kinds of color blindness except monochromacy.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png" alt="Make your charts color blind friendly: try to use a single hue palette or a red-yellow-blue palette if the usage of color is inevitable." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-hue-color-palette.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p><strong>Use color for groups,</strong> not the individual categories. By doing that the number of colors will be reduced, as well as visual clutter and the possibility of color confusion.</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png" alt="Make your charts color blind friendly: use color for groups, not the individual categories." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-group-color.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;">&nbsp;</h2>
<a id="good-bad-charts" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;">Good and bad charts for color blind viewers</h2>
<p>Most of the charts can be modified to be colorblind-friendly, the difference is that some of the charts won’t suffer from the lack of color while the others are heavily dependent on color. Our recommendations are based on how easily one or the other chart can work without any color coding.<br><br></p>
<a id="comparison-charts" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h3 style="font-size: 24px;">Comparison charts</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>✅ Good choice: Dot plot (and Parallel coordinates)</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png" alt="Dot plots (and parallel coordinates) are the best choice when it comes to comparison charts, especially for those with multiple categories at the same time." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-dot-plot.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Dot plot could be both great and challenging. If the color is used for dot differentiation – it won’t work well. But if the dots are substituted with different colors per category it will make a very good choice for comparison of multiple categories at the same time.</p>
<p>Check <a href="/product/chart-library/dot-plot" rel="noopener" target="_blank">this</a> resource page and learn how to design the best dot plots that will impress your audience.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>❌&nbsp;Bad choice: Grouped bar/column chart</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png" alt="Grouped bar/column charts are not the best choice when it comes to comparison charts, since they are too much based on the color differences of the bars of the same group." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-grouped-bar-chart.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Grouped bar charts are usually based on the color differences of the bars of the same group. This makes it difficult to read for colorblind users. With a large number of categories, this chart becomes unreadable to everyone.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="correlation-charts" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h3 style="font-size: 24px;">Correlation charts</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>✅ Good choice: Bubble chart</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png" alt="Bubble charts are the best choice when it comes to correlation charts, since they can easily be used without color." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-scatterplot.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>It can be easily used without color. X- and Y- axes, size, and different icons provide 4 dimensions already which is easily enough for most of the visualization tasks.</p>
<p>➡️ <a href="https://insights.datylon.com/auth/join" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Datylon chart maker allows you to create beautiful bubble charts. Give it a try for free!</a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>❌ Bad choice: Heatmap</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png" alt="Heatmaps are not the best choice when it comes to correlation charts, since they are heavily dependent on color." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-heatmap.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Heatmaps are heavily dependent on color, so the only way to make it safe for colorblind readers is to use one hue or grayscale palette.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="part-to-whole-charts" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h3 style="font-size: 24px;">Part-to-whole &amp; hierarchical charts</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>✅ Good choice: Icon array</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png" alt="Icon arrays are the best choice when it comes to part-to-whole &amp; hierarchical charts, since they do not depend on colored areas or sectors." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-icon-array.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Icon array is a rare case of a part-to-whole chart that doesn’t depend on colored areas or sectors. With the use of icons instead of color differentiation, this chart becomes a preferable chart type for colorblind people among all part-to-whole charts.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>❌ Bad choice: Treemap</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png" alt="Treemaps are not the best choice when it comes to part-to-whole &amp; hierarchical charts, since they are heavily dependent on color." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-treemap.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Similar to heatmaps, treemaps are famous for their extensive use of color. Surely, a treemap can be made also with a mono hue palette or just with the help of stroke borders, but the lack of color will weaken its visual strength, especially if a complex hierarchical structure should be presented. One of the things that can save a treemap is spacing between cells.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="data-over-time-charts" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h3 style="font-size: 24px;">Date over time charts</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>✅ Good choice: Line chart</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png" alt="Line charts are the best choice when it comes to date over time charts, since they can be modified in various ways to make it color blind friendly." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-line-chart.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The simplest and most flexible temporal chart that can be modified in various ways to make it readable for a colorblind audience. In the case of multiple categories, the line width can be modified as well as various types of dashed strokes. Direct labels and data marks can also be used to differentiate lines. Discover even more pro design tips on our dedicated <a href="/product/chart-library/line-chart" rel="noopener" target="_blank">line chart resource page</a> and advance your data visualization with Datylon.</p>
<p>You can also easily create colorblind-friendly line charts with the Datylon chart maker. Sign up for free using <a href="https://insights.datylon.com/auth/join" rel="noopener" target="_blank">this</a> link.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>❌ Bad choice: Streamgraph</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png" alt="Streamgraphs are not the best choice when it comes to date over time charts, since they are helpless without color." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-streamgraph.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A very beautiful chart, but helpless without color. It loses its attractiveness and readability right away.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="distribution" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h3 style="font-size: 24px;">Distribution</h3>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>✅ Good choice: Density and ridgeline plots</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png" alt="Density and ridgeline plots are the best choice when it comes to distributive charts, since opacity and direct labels can substitute the need for coloring." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-density-plot.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A good choice for visualizing both single and multiple distributions. Opacity and direct labels can substitute the need for coloring.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4>❌ Bad choice: One-dimensional heatmap</h4>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img src="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png" alt="One-dimensional heatmaps are not the best choice when it comes to distributive charts, excepted if you use a one hue palette." width="720" loading="lazy" style="width: 720px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; display: block;" srcset="https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=360&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png 360w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=720&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png 720w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=1080&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png 1080w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=1440&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png 1440w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=1800&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png 1800w, https://www.datylon.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Datylon%20Website2020/Blogs/The%20best%20charts%20for%20color%20blind%20viewers/datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png?width=2160&amp;name=datylon-blog-best-charts-for-color-blind-viewers-one-dim-heatmap.png 2160w" sizes="(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"></p>
<p>A one-dimensional heatmap can quickly become a bad choice if multiple colors are used. One hue palette can work pretty well though.<br><br></p>
<a id="further-reading-resources" data-hs-anchor="true"></a>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;">Further reading and resources</h2>
<ul style="line-height: 1.5;">
<li><span style="font-size: 18px;"><a href="/blog/mind-your-data-visualization-brain-capacity" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Mind your data visualization</a> - How to present your data effectively by getting the most out of your reader's brain capacity.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 18px;"><a href="/blog/9-types-of-data-visualization" rel="noopener" target="_blank">9 types of data visualization</a> - How to choose the right type for the right audience.</span></li>
<li><span style="font-size: 18px;"><a href="/product/chart-library" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Datylon Chart Library</a> - Pro design tips to make the best charts and graphs and take your data visualization to the next level.</span><br><span style="font-size: 18px;"></span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size: 18px;">➡️ If you want to apply all these tips and make your data visualizations truly inclusive for different types of audiences, you need the full freedom of design to do so. Thankfully, you can do it with Datylon. Sign up using <a href="https://insights.datylon.com/auth/join" rel="noopener" target="_blank">this</a> link - it's free and only takes a few seconds.</span><span style="font-size: 18px;"></span></p>
